+# Phase 2: GDN graph-level fusion (alpha / beta / conv)
+
+Track B follow-on for Qwen3.5 linear-attention decode on HIP/CUDA (`ggml-cuda.cu`).
+
+## Implemented fusions
+
+### B2 — `SSM_CONV + SILU` (verified + hardened)
+
+**Graph:** `build_layer_attn_linear()` → `ggml_ssm_conv` → `ggml_silu`.
+
+**Matcher:** Existing `ggml_cuda_can_fuse({ SSM_CONV, UNARY(SILU) })` plus new
+`ggml_cuda_ssm_conv_silu_span()` that skips view/noop nodes between conv and silu
+(same pattern as `ggml_cuda_try_gdn_decode_megafusion`).
+
+**Kernel:** `ggml_cuda_op_ssm_conv(..., silu_dst)` in `ssm-conv.cu`.
+
+### B3 — GDN alpha gate: `ADD + SOFTPLUS (+ MUL)`
+
+**Graph:** `alpha + ssm_dt` → `softplus` → `mul(ssm_a)` in `qwen35.cpp`.
+
+**Matcher:** `ggml_cuda_can_fuse({ ADD, UNARY(SOFTPLUS), MUL })` with 1-D channel-wise
+`ssm_dt` / `ssm_a` broadcast (ne[0] == num_v_heads).
+
+**Kernel:** `ggml_cuda_op_add_softplus_mul` in `unary.cu` — one launch for
+`softplus(x + bias) * gate`.
+
+Fallback: `ADD + SOFTPLUS` only when the downstream mul is not fuseable.
+
+### B4 — GDN beta: `MUL_MAT + SIGMOID` (not fused)
+
+Beta path is `mul_mat → reshape → sigmoid`. Reshape is a graph no-op at runtime;
+fusing sigmoid into the quantized matmul epilogue is deferred (needs mm kernel hook).
+
+Separate `UNARY(SIGMOID)` still runs as a single kernel after matmul.
+
+### Megafusion (optional, env-gated)
+
+`GGML_CUDA_GDN_DECODE_FUSED=1` enables `gated_delta_net_decode_fused.cu` megafusion:
+conv + silu + L2 + one GDN step (Qwythos decode, S_v=128, d_conv=4, n_tokens=1).
+Default off; Phase 2 micro-fusions above apply when megafusion is disabled.
+
+## Tests
